Differential gene expression

Differential Expression (DE) performing statistical analysis to discover quantitative changes in expression levels between experimental groups.

Tidybulk

Tidybulk is a Bioconductor package that takes together the methods from three popular DE (edgeR, DESeq2 and limma) and simplifies the analysis

The pipeline

  1. Load libraries
  2. Load tables
  3. Prepare dataset
  4. Inspect pre-normalization
  5. Normalize
  6. Inspect post-normalization
  7. Differential expression

Only chromosome X

4 - Explore dataset

We can inspect thousands of genes in a single 2-dimensional plot so we need to apply a dimension reduction method.

Tidybulk comes with three:

  • PCA: Principal Component Analysis (1901)
  • MDS: Multi-Dimensional Scaling (2001?)
  • t-SNE: t-distributed Stochastic Neighbor Embedding (2008)

4.1 PCA

pca <-
  counts %>%
  identify_abundant() %>%
  reduce_dimensions(method = "PCA")

5. Normalize data

Normalizations consists of:

  • Removing genes with low expression (in all or a group of samples)
  • Take into account the library sizes
  • Add, remove and scale the counts

to make the values comparable between groups

Normalize with tidybulk

counts_normalized <-
  counts %>%
  identify_abundant(
    factor_of_interest = sex,
    minimum_counts = 2,
    minimum_proportion = 0.7
  ) %>%
  keep_abundant(factor_of_interest = sex) %>%
  scale_abundance() %>%
  adjust_abundance(~ sex + population)

7. Differential expression

differential_expression <-
  counts_normalized %>%
  test_differential_abundance(
    ~ 0 + sex + population,
    contrasts = "sexfemale - sexmale"
  ) %>%
  pivot_transcript()

7.1 MA-plot (logCPM vs logFC)

ma_plot <-
  data_de_plot %>%
  ggplot(aes(
    x = logCPM, y = logFC,
    label = label,
    color = color,
    size = significant,
    alpha = significant
  )) +
  geom_point() +
  ggrepel::geom_text_repel()

7.2 Volcano plot (logFC vs FDR)

volcano_plot <-
  data_de_plot %>%
  ggplot(aes(
    x = logFC, y = FDR, 
    label = label, 
    color = color,
    size = significant,
    alpha = significant
  )) +
  geom_point() +
  ggrepel::geom_text_repel() +
  scale_y_continuous(trans = "log10_reverse")
